  "2026-05-21T04:42:28.101Z",codex-full-manual-audit,"Pause evidence: focused subset fixed and release-gated. Fixed config list shorthand, calendar positional view handling, GC missing-reindex guidance, PM_NO_TELEMETRY opt-out reporting/runtime, invalid dependency kind recovery, close active-child warning, and extension contract metadata/alias dedupe. Remaining backlog items on this chore stay open: init verbosity, help alias display bloat, create changed_fields noise, calendar include scheduled doc drift, guide install hints, priority wording drift, template starter content, broader default-safety review, and event equal-timestamp hinting. Full gate passed with run-gates telemetry-mode required and 100% selected coverage."
  "2026-05-21T05:03:41.138Z",codex-full-manual-audit,"PR review response evidence: addressed valid CodeRabbit/Sourcery feedback by shifting config shorthand keys correctly, validating extension flag value_type fallback before using valueName string fallback, making merged extension x-extension-command deterministic while exposing x-extension-commands, merging duplicate flag metadata predictably, using merged extension contracts for action descriptors and alias-aware command catalog, and adding PM_NO_TELEMETRY health coverage. Focused review-fix suite passed: 3 files, 26 tests; tsc --noEmit passed."
  "2026-05-21T05:12:26.530Z",codex-full-manual-audit,"CI fix evidence: PR run 26206567968 exposed alias availability regression where merged command_path values like cal|calendar and test-runs aliases were treated as one literal command. Fixed contract command-path matching, scoped-command derivation, and extension availability to split alias groups. Verification passed: calendar/contracts/health focused suite 64 tests, tsc --noEmit, and node scripts/dogfood-package-first.mjs 84 commands."
  "2026-05-21T18:19:29.355Z",codex-extensive-audit,"Evidence: implemented remaining safe polish fixes from backlog: create no longer reports body in changed_fields when body was omitted, calendar package help/completions now document accepted scheduled include alias, and create/update equal --event start/end timestamps now explain that equality is invalid and how to recover. Focused suite passed: 5 files / 208 tests. Manual temp smoke passed after installing calendar + guide-shell in isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH; verified compact create changed_fields, equal event recovery, calendar help scheduled alias, and completion scheduled alias."
  "2026-05-21T18:29:13.488Z",codex-extensive-audit,"PR evidence: opened draft PR #38 for the agent UX/Sentry/privacy polish branch. Required 15-minute AI review window started at 2026-05-21T20:29:07+02:00; CI was in progress at PR creation."
  "2026-05-21T18:37:36.373Z",codex-extensive-audit,"PR review evidence: marked PR #38 ready for review and explicitly triggered CodeRabbit and Sourcery at 2026-05-21T20:37:16+02:00. Will hold at least 15 minutes before merge and inspect bot feedback before finalizing."
  "2026-05-21T18:45:33.095Z",codex-extensive-audit,"PR review response evidence: addressed Sourcery and CodeRabbit feedback by moving the equal event start/end recovery text into a shared command message, tightening getGlobalOptions through a small command-options reader helper, and renaming the registration-helper fallback test. Kept whitespace body semantics unchanged because explicit whitespace body content is still user-supplied content; the compact-output fix only omits the default empty body. Targeted review-fix suite passed: 3 files / 89 tests."
  "2026-05-21T18:47:18.772Z",codex-extensive-audit,"Verification evidence: after adding the shared event validation message module, release-readiness coverage alignment correctly flagged the new source file as intentionally outside the covered include set. Updated the alignment expectation and reran the focused suite successfully: 5 files / 208 tests."
  "2026-05-21T18:54:18.155Z",codex-extensive-audit,"Final PR review evidence: after follow-up commit 7998323, GitHub CI run 26246268622 passed build foundation, Ubuntu test, macOS test, coverage, typecheck, static, compat, and smokes. Sourcery review passed. CodeRabbit completed review; actionable implementation nit was already fixed, and remaining pm-system-of-record comments were verified as false positives because the changed pm artifacts were generated by pm commands. Gemini optional-chaining suggestion was reviewed and declined because the explicit CommandOptionsReader helper avoids any casts while keeping the same behavior."
  "2026-05-23T17:11:42.209Z",help-output-subagent,"help-output-subagent START: L1 (concise pm init default + --verbose full tree) and L4 (hide pure snake_case underscore-duplicate aliases from --help while keeping them parse-functional). Plan: L4 uses commander new Option(flags,desc).hideHelp() in register-mutation.ts registerCommanderOptionContracts for aliasOptions whose long == kebab-canonical with - replaced by _; also hide hand-written snake aliases in register-mutation (allow_audit_update etc.), update-many block, plan block, schema block, and register-list-query (--assignee_filter, --include_unparented). KEEP semantic aliases visible (--fail-on-warn, --local, --active-only, --ac, --rank, --estimate). L1 adds --verbose to init and gates the full settings tree behind it. JSON help payload unchanged (reads command.options which hideHelp keeps). Running focused specs next."
  "2026-05-23T17:24:21.349Z",help-output-subagent,"help-output-subagent DONE (L1+L4 both complete).\n\nL4 (snake-alias help bloat): RULE = hide an alias only when its long flag is the underscore form of an existing kebab long flag (normalize both flags by replacing interior hyphens with underscores; equal + non-identical => hidden). Multi-long-flag specs are matched against EVERY long flag (so --estimated_minutes hides under '--estimate, --estimated-minutes'). Semantic/word aliases stay visible (--ac, --rank, --step, --decision, --discovery, --validation, --fail-on-warn, --local, --active-only). Mechanism: commander new Option(flags,desc).hideHelp() (repeatable ones get .argParser(collect)); option stays in command.options so JSON help payload + completion are unchanged, only text --help omits it; parse-time aliases still populate their option keys. New pure-logic helper src/core/shared/option-alias-visibility.ts (isPureSnakeCaseAlias/extractLongFlag/extractLongFlags) added to vitest include at 100% coverage.\n\nL1 (concise pm init): added --verbose flag; default toon output now a concise summary (path, id_prefix, governance_preset, telemetry.enabled+capture_level, output_format, created_dirs+count, ALL warnings incl already_exists:, wizard_used, installed_packages, next_steps, agent_guidance, hint). Full settings tree only with --verbose OR --json (JSON shape unchanged for consumers). summarizeInitResult() in init.ts. Measured: pm init 193 -> 60 lines default; --verbose still 193; --json unchanged (settings present).\n\nFiles changed: src/cli/commands/init.ts (summarizeInitResult + InitConciseResult), src/cli/commands/index.ts (export), src/cli/register-setup.ts (init --verbose + gate), src/cli/register-mutation.ts (addHiddenOption + hide create/update via contracts + update-many/plan/schema/update hand-written snake aliases), src/cli/register-list-query.ts (hide --assignee_filter on list/aggregate/context, --include_unparented on aggregate), src/core/shared/option-alias-visibility.ts (NEW helper), vitest.config.ts (include helper). Tests: tests/unit/option-alias-visibility.spec.ts (NEW), tests/unit/init-command.spec.ts (+summary tests), tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts (+init concise/verbose + alias-hiding regression).\n\nTests run (all PASS): option-alias-visibility 16; init-command 8; help-runtime 27; completion 212-total batch (completion/contracts/create/update/task-lifecycle); update-many/list/schema/close 43; cli.integration+governance 78; structure-exports+bootstrap-args 39. tsc --noEmit clean. Helper coverage 100% stmts/branch/funcs/lines.\n\nCOORDINATOR SHARED-FILE TODOs (I did NOT touch these - all forbidden in my scope):\n1. CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased]: add 'Concise pm init default output (full settings tree now behind --verbose; --json unchanged)' and 'Hidden pure snake_case underscore-duplicate option aliases from --help across mutation/list commands (still functional as parse-time aliases)'.\n2. docs/COMMANDS + docs/AGENT_GUIDE: optionally document pm init --verbose and that snake aliases are hidden-but-functional.\n3. completion.ts (bash/zsh/fish hand-maintained): snake aliases still listed there - functionally harmless (still parse) but for consistency the coordinator may prune --foo_bar completion entries. Not required.\n4. SDK contracts (src/sdk/cli-contracts*): NO change needed - I hid via registration only, contract data untouched; existing help-runtime JSON assertion (--blocked_by absent / --blocked-by aliases include --blocked_by) still passes."
  "2026-05-23T17:28:48.239Z",cli-input-subagent,"START [cli-input-ergonomics sub-agent] Beginning L8/L7/L9 from pm-5k2w. Plan: L8 shared priority resolver in src/core/item/priority.ts (mapping critical=0,high=1,medium=2,low=3,minimal=4; numeric 0..4 still valid; bad input throws USAGE listing both forms), called from create.ts ensurePriority + update.ts ensurePriority. L7 add concrete command->package install hint in error-guidance.ts unknown_command block (guide->@unbrained/pm-guide-shell via 'pm install guide-shell'; templates->@unbrained/pm-templates via 'pm install templates'; calendar/cal->@unbrained/pm-calendar via 'pm install calendar'); keep existing fields. L9 ship BUILTIN starter templates (bug/feature/spike/chore) in packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts so 'pm templates' returns count>0 out of the box; user-saved templates override builtins; mirror into runtime.js. Not touching files owned by the concurrent agent/coordinator."
  "2026-05-23T17:37:19.755Z",cli-input-subagent,"DONE [cli-input-ergonomics sub-agent] L8/L7/L9 all complete; tsc (main+packages) clean; focused specs pass.\n\nL8 (named priority aliases): shared resolver src/core/item/priority.ts -> resolvePriority(raw): Priority. Mapping critical=0, high=1, medium=2, low=3, minimal=4 (case-insensitive, trims ws). Numeric 0..4 unchanged (strict /^[0-4]$/ after trim; rejects 1.0/5/-1). Bad/empty input throws PmCliError USAGE: 'Invalid priority \"X\". Accepted values: numbers 0..4 (0=critical, 1=high, 2=medium, 3=low, 4=minimal) or names (critical, high, medium, low, minimal), case-insensitive.' Also exports PRIORITY_NAME_TO_VALUE + PRIORITY_ACCEPTED_FORMS_HINT. Wired from create.ts ensurePriority() and update.ts ensurePriority() (both now just delegate to resolvePriority). Added priority.ts to vitest include; 100% cover (13/13 stmts, 6/6 branch, 2/2 func).\n\nL7 (install hint for known package commands): added KNOWN_PACKAGE_COMMAND_HINTS catalog + resolveKnownPackageCommandHint() in src/cli/error-guidance.ts; emits concrete hint in the unknown_command branch of buildCommanderErrorGuidance (~line 682). Catalog: guide->@unbrained/pm-guide-shell ('pm install guide-shell'); templates->@unbrained/pm-templates ('pm install templates'); calendar & cal->@unbrained/pm-calendar ('pm install calendar'). Keeps all existing fields; install command added to examples (deduped, first) + next_steps (first), and package name woven into title/required/why. Non-package unknown commands unchanged. Note: a generic optional-package hint already lived in src/cli/commander-usage.ts (FORBIDDEN file, not touched) so the generic line still trails; my concrete hint leads. Added dedupeStrings() helper.\n\nL9 (builtin starter templates): implemented in packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts (+ mirrored runtime.js). BUILTIN_TEMPLATES = bug (type=Issue, priority=1, acceptance/expected/actual + repro body), feature (type=Feature, priority=2, whyNow + goal body), spike (type=Task, priority=2, estimatedMinutes=120, timeboxed body), chore (type=Chore, priority=3). Option keys are camelCase create keys so 'pm create --template <name>' merges them directly. runTemplatesList now merges user+builtin (user shadows same-name builtin) and returns {templates,count,builtin_templates,user_templates}. runTemplatesShow returns {name,source:'builtin'|'user',...,path}; builtins use path 'builtin:<name>' and ts 1970-01-01. New resolveTemplateDocument()/readUserTemplateNames()/builtinTemplateDocument(); save still preserves user created_at via the original readStoredTemplateDocument. NOTE: core SDK fallback src/cli/commands/templates.ts (used only when package not installed) was NOT changed — its loadCreateTemplateOptions/runTemplatesList have no builtins. Since 'pm templates' is package-provided (unknown without the package, see L7), builtins only need to live in the package runtime. Flagging in case the coordinator wants parity in the SDK fallback.\n\nFILES CHANGED (mine):\n- NEW src/core/item/priority.ts\n- src/cli/commands/create.ts (import + ensurePriority delegates)\n- src/cli/commands/update.ts (import + ensurePriority delegates)\n- src/cli/error-guidance.ts (catalog + resolver + dedupeStrings + unknown_command hint)\n- packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts AND runtime.js (builtins; behavior-identical mirrors)\n- vitest.config.ts (added src/core/item/priority.ts to include only)\n- NEW tests/unit/priority.spec.ts\n- tests/unit/error-guidance.spec.ts (+2 cases: install-hint, no-hint-for-unknown)\n- tests/unit/templates-command.spec.ts (+3 cases: builtins list, create-from-builtin, user-override)\n\nTESTS (PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1, --reporter=dot): priority 8 PASS; error-guidance 9 PASS; templates-command 9 PASS (6 old + 3 new); create-command + update-command + update-many 112 PASS; completion + contracts + cli.integration 180 PASS. priority.ts coverage 100%. tsc --noEmit (tsconfig.json) clean; tsc -p tsconfig.packages.json clean.\n\nMANUAL VERIFY (temp PM_PATH, minimal preset): create --priority high=>1, --priority 2=>2, Critical=>0, MINIMAL=>4, bogus=>USAGE error listing both forms; update --priority high=>1, badword=>same error. pm guide (uninstalled) => title/required/why name @unbrained/pm-guide-shell, examples+next_steps include 'pm install guide-shell'; pm cal => @unbrained/pm-calendar / 'pm install calendar'; pm templates (uninstalled) => @unbrained/pm-templates / 'pm install templates'. After 'pm install templates --project': pm templates --json => count 4 (bug,chore,feature,spike); show spike => source:builtin; create --template bug (no save) => Issue/priority 1; saving user 'bug' then show => source:user/type=Task, list shows bug once (user_templates), builtin_templates drops bug.\n\nCOORDINATOR SHARED-FILE TODOs (I did NOT touch these):\n1. CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased]: add (a) '--priority now accepts named levels (critical/high/medium/low/minimal, case-insensitive) in create and update; numeric 0..4 still works'; (b) 'Unknown package-provided commands (guide/templates/calendar/cal) now show a concrete install command'; (c) 'pm templates ships builtin starter templates (bug/feature/spike/chore) so the catalog is non-empty out of the box; user templates override builtins'.\n2. docs/COMMANDS + docs/AGENT_GUIDE: document named priority aliases; document builtin templates + that pm templates show now returns a source field and list returns builtin_templates/user_templates.\n3. completion.ts (bash/zsh/fish): optional — could add builtin template names (bug/feature/spike/chore) to 'templates show' value completion; not required.\n4. SDK contracts (src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts): no change strictly needed (priority option still a string; resolver runs at execution). If contract docs describe priority as 'numeric 0..4', update the description to mention named aliases. templates-show/list result schema (if documented in contracts) now has extra fields (source/builtin_templates/user_templates) — additive.\n5. Consider whether src/cli/commands/templates.ts (SDK fallback) should also ship builtins for parity (currently only the package runtime has them)."
  "2026-05-23T18:16:11.550Z",codex-active-work,"Completion evidence 2026-05-23: remaining open low-severity backlog from this chore is now resolved through plan pm-fuat and decision pm-tobi plus templates dedup pm-ypqp. Implemented L1 concise init, L4 hidden pure snake help aliases, L7 package install hints, L8 named priorities, L9 starter templates, and L10 delete dry-run/gc help. Final verification passed full release gate with 100% coverage and required Sentry/telemetry. Leaving item status unchanged here because it is claimed by claude-code-agent, not this coordinator claim."
