  "2026-05-25T08:22:35.797Z",config-ux-subagent,"config-ux-subagent START: FIX A — add optional [value] positional to config cmd (register-setup.ts) + new pure helper src/core/config/positional-value.ts (resolveConfigPositionalValue) routing key→typed flag (format/policy/criterion) with off/on/true/false synonyms; wire into runConfig only when typed flag not already passed, conflict=error, context=hint. FIX B — shrink invalid-key error to canonical kebab forms + '(underscore variants also accepted)'. New unit spec at 100% cov, add helper to vitest include. Verify tsc + tests + smoke."
  "2026-05-25T08:32:31.586Z",config-ux-subagent,"config-ux-subagent DONE (FIX A + FIX B both complete; item left open per instructions).\n\nFIX A (positional value for `pm config set <key> <value>`):\n- NEW pure helper src/core/config/positional-value.ts exporting resolveConfigPositionalValue(keyOrAlias, value) -> discriminated union. Accepts BOTH kebab and snake key forms (normalizes interior '-' to '_'). Mapping table:\n  * item-format -> {flag:'format', value} (verbatim)\n  * definition-of-done, metadata-required-fields, lifecycle-stale-blocker-reason-patterns, lifecycle-closure-like-blocked-reason-patterns, lifecycle-closure-like-resolution-patterns, lifecycle-closure-like-actual-result-patterns -> {flag:'criterion', values:[value]}\n  * history-missing-stream-policy, sprint-release-format-policy, parent-reference-policy, metadata-validation-profile, governance-preset, governance-ownership-enforcement, governance-create-mode-default, governance-close-validation-default, governance-parent-reference-policy, governance-metadata-validation-profile, governance-force-required-for-stale-lock, test-result-tracking, telemetry-tracking -> {flag:'policy', value}. For the three enabled/disabled-valued keys (governance-force-required-for-stale-lock, test-result-tracking, telemetry-tracking) the synonyms off->disabled, on->enabled, true->enabled, false->disabled (case-insensitive) are applied; all other policy keys pass the value through unchanged so existing validators keep their good error messages.\n  * context -> {routable:false, reason: hint naming --default-depth/--activity-limit/--stale-threshold-days/--section-<name>}\n  * unknown key -> {routable:false} (caller hits the FIX-B invalid-key error first since normalizeKey runs before routing)\n- Wired in src/cli/commands/config.ts: new optional 6th param valueValue on runConfig; private applyPositionalValue(action,key,value,options) injects the routed flag into options ONLY when (a) action==='set', (b) key present, (c) the typed flag was NOT already supplied. If the explicit flag matches the positional -> no-op; if it conflicts -> clear USAGE error; positional on non-set action or with no key -> clear USAGE error; context -> hint error. All existing typed-flag behavior 100% intact (back-compat verified).\n- register-setup.ts: added 4th positional [value] argument + help text; action handler now resolves value with shorthand-scope shift (config set <key> <value> => action=set,key,value; config project set <key> <value> also works) and passes resolvedValue as 6th arg.\n- MCP parity: src/mcp/server.ts config case now passes readString(args/options,'value') as 6th arg; src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts config schema-contract optional list gains 'value' (param 'value' already typed in props map).\n\nFIX B (token-heavy invalid-key error): src/cli/commands/config.ts normalizeKey now lists CANONICAL_CONFIG_KEYS (21 kebab forms derived from CONFIG_KEY_ALIASES[k][0]) + '(underscore variants also accepted)' instead of all ~45 kebab+snake CONFIG_KEY_VALUES. Snake forms still fully accepted as input. No other code/tests depended on the old exact string (only assertion was exitCode===USAGE).\n\nFILES CHANGED:\n- NEW src/core/config/positional-value.ts (in vitest include @100% cover)\n- src/cli/commands/config.ts (import, CANONICAL_CONFIG_KEYS, applyPositionalValue, runConfig 6th param, shortened error)\n- src/cli/register-setup.ts ([value] arg + handler wiring + shorthand shift)\n- src/mcp/server.ts (config value pass-through)\n- src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts (config optional += 'value')\n- vitest.config.ts (added positional-value.ts to coverage include only; NOT exclude)\n- docs/CONFIGURATION.md (documented positional value form + context-uses-flags note)\n- NEW tests/unit/config-positional-value.spec.ts (8 tests, helper @100%)\n- tests/unit/config-command.spec.ts (+10 wiring tests)\n\nTESTS (all PASS): config-positional-value 8; config-command 36 (was 26, +10); helper coverage 100% stmts(22/22)/branch(18/18)/funcs(3/3)/lines. Broader: help-runtime 27 + completion 212-batch (163 across 4 files); release-readiness-runtime 32 (coverage-alignment + config gate green); contracts-command + mcp-dynamic-package-actions + claude-plugin-contract 34; structure-exports + bootstrap-args + cli.integration 114. tsc --noEmit (tsconfig.json) clean. docs-skills gate PASS. (packages untouched, tsconfig.packages.json not needed.)\n\nMANUAL SMOKE (pnpm build once; /tmp/cfgprobe, init --defaults): `config set telemetry-tracking off`->policy disabled changed:true; `... disabled`->changed:false; `... item-format toon`->format toon; `... governance-preset strict`->policy strict changed:true; `... definition-of-done \"Tests pass\"`->criteria [\"Tests pass\"]. `config set bogus-key foo`-> shortened 21-key error + underscore note. `config set context deep`-> not-routable hint (flags listed; error layer even auto-added suggested_retry). `config set telemetry-tracking off --policy enabled`-> conflict USAGE error. Back-compat `config set telemetry-tracking --policy enabled` and `config project set telemetry-tracking on` both work.\n\nCOORDINATOR TODOs (shared files I did NOT touch):\n1. CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] (forbidden for me): add\n   - 'pm config set <key> <value> now accepts the value as a positional argument, routed to the correct typed flag (--policy/--format/--criterion) by key; off/on/true/false map to disabled/enabled for boolean policy keys.'\n   - 'Shortened the invalid config-key error to list canonical kebab keys only (underscore variants still accepted).'\n2. docs: COMMANDS.md/AGENT_GUIDE.md were left as-is (no existing `config set` detail there; CONFIGURATION.md is the canonical home and was updated). Optional to cross-link.\n3. completion.ts NOT changed (config values are not value-completed there; positional is free-form). No action required."
